# intraday-x — copy to `.env` and fill in. NEVER commit your real .env (it's gitignored).
# We use FREE, NON-BROKER data vendors only. No broker integrations.

# --- Twelve Data (FREE, non-broker; the recommended free upgrade from yfinance) -
# Free tier, NO credit card: https://twelvedata.com/  → API key in the dashboard.
# Gives 1-minute bars back to 2020 + multi-year 5-minute (yfinance only has ~7/60
# days). Limits: ~800 requests/day, 8/min. Wired + preferred over yfinance when set.
TWELVEDATA_API_KEY=

# --- Polygon.io (optional; full-market data vendor, not a broker) --------------
# Free tier at https://polygon.io/ (~2yr, 5 req/min). If set, the composite
# router auto-prefers Polygon. No code needed — the provider is already wired.
POLYGON_API_KEY=

# --- Financial Modeling Prep (optional; non-broker data vendor) ---------------
# Paid subscription at https://financialmodelingprep.com/developer/.
# Provides intraday (1min/5min/etc.) and daily bars. Add the key in Settings.
FMP_API_KEY=

# --- Frontend (optional) -----------------------------------------------------
# In dev the Vite proxy forwards /api + /ws to the backend on :8000, so no env
# is required. For a split deployment, point the dashboard at the API:
# PUBLIC_API_BASE=https://your-api-host
# PUBLIC_WS_URL=wss://your-api-host/ws/signals
